Course gives knowledge about the general principles and ethics of scientific investigations, about safety regulations related to the work in laboratory, about scientific methodology and statistics. Course gives basic knowledge about principles of antigen-antibody interactions in immunological test prototypes. Students are acknowledged about ongoing scientific projects in the Chair. Students are oblidged to write an essay about a topic related to one of lab's scientific projects. Their task is also to determine antibody status in a patients' group as well as among controls and to analyse the results and present a topic on Chair's seminar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To get general principles of research in immunology (I stage).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course, within the syllabus, a student:  1. knows principles of research ethics taking into account specific aspects in immunology; 2. is acquainted with expanded up-to-date knowledge about immunology and it's research methods; 3. is able critically analyze the modern immunological literature in a specific field and is able to write about this a scientific review;  4. present these data in a short concise oral presentation in special seminar.
